# OpenClaw .env example
#
# Quick start:
# 1) Copy this file to `.env` (for local runs from this repo), OR to `~/.openclaw/.env` (for launchd/systemd daemons).
# 2) Fill only the values you use.
# 3) Keep real secrets out of git.
#
# Env-source precedence for environment variables (highest -> lowest):
# process env, ./.env, ~/.openclaw/.env, then openclaw.json `env` block.
# Existing non-empty process env vars are not overridden by dotenv/config env loading.
# Note: direct config keys (for example `gateway.auth.token` or channel tokens in openclaw.json)
# are resolved separately from env loading and often take precedence over env fallbacks.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Gateway auth + paths
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Recommended if the gateway binds beyond loopback.
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-long-random-token
# Example generator: openssl rand -hex 32
# You can reference the same value from openclaw.json as: "token": "${OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN}"

# Optional alternative auth mode (use token OR password).
# OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD=change-me-to-a-strong-password

# Optional path overrides (defaults shown for reference).
# OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=~/.openclaw
# OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=~/.openclaw/openclaw.json
# OPENCLAW_HOME=~

# Windows launchers (Start-TUI.ps1, Start-Gateway.ps1): default = repo (transcripts under logs/launcher).
# Set to 0 to use .openclaw-desktop for OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH and logs under .openclaw-desktop/logs.
# OPENCLAW_USE_REPO_LAUNCHER=0

# Optional: import missing keys from your login shell profile.
# OPENCLAW_LOAD_SHELL_ENV=1
# OPENCLAW_SHELL_ENV_TIMEOUT_MS=15000

# Optional: Windows launcher `scripts/launchers/start_ngrok.ps1` uses repo-local ngrok only (e.g. bin/ngrok.exe).
# Set this if your binary lives outside the default search paths.
# NGROK_EXE=C:\full\path\to\ngrok.exe
# Optional: explicit ngrok upstream (default http://127.0.0.1:<gateway port> when unset).
# OpenClaw public URL + LINE webhook: tunnel MUST target the Gateway (usually :18789), NOT Hypura (:8080).
# Do not point NGROK_UPSTREAM_URL at http://127.0.0.1:8080 unless you only expose inference; webhooks will break.
# Telegram webhook mode uses a separate listener (default path /telegram-webhook, port 8787) — then set:
# NGROK_UPSTREAM_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8787
# When upstream is the Telegram listener port, launchers sync OPENCLAW_PUBLIC_URL + TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_URL only (LINE_WEBHOOK_URL is left unchanged).
# LINE webhook URL on the gateway is {OPENCLAW_PUBLIC_URL}/line/webhook (not /hooks/line).
# NGROK_UPSTREAM_URL=https://127.0.0.1:8443
# Recommended for LINE + Gateway: omit NGROK_UPSTREAM_URL, or NGROK_UPSTREAM_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18789

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Hypura 0.4.x (GGUF inference, Ollama-compatible API on :8080; binary name `hypura`)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Full path to the Gemma / other .gguf file. Required for `launch-desktop-stack` to auto-start Hypura.
# CLI shape: hypura serve <model.gguf> [--port 8080] [--context 4096]
# Example (user downl): full path to the GGUF you serve with hypura
# HAKUA_HYPURA_GGUF=C:\Users\downl\Desktop\SO8T\gguf_models\stronman\Gemma-4-E4B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive\Gemma-4-E4B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive-Q4_K_M.gguf
# HYPURA_GGUF=...   (alias)
# HYPURA_PORT=8080
# HYPURA_CONTEXT=32768
# When hypura is not on PATH, set full path to the release binary:
# HAKUA_HYPURA_EXE=C:\Users\downl\Desktop\hypura-main\hypura-main\target\release\hypura.exe
# HYPURA_EXE=...   (alias)
# When openclaw.json uses models.providers.hypura.apiKey "${HYPURA_API_KEY}" (recommended).
# HYPURA_API_KEY=hypura-local
# When openclaw.json uses models.providers.ollama.apiKey "${OLLAMA_API_KEY}".
# Local Ollama: use the OpenClaw marker (any non-empty dummy works; this is the documented default).
# OLLAMA_API_KEY=ollama-local
# Ollama Cloud / remote with real auth: set your actual API key instead.
# After serve: powershell -File scripts\tools\show-hypura-model-name.ps1
# Then set agents.defaults.model.primary to hypura/<exact name from /api/tags>

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker Compose (docker-compose.yml) — bind-mount sources; must be non-empty for `docker compose up`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Host paths published into the gateway container. Relative paths are resolved from the repo root.
# Sovereign-Portal.ps1 (-Mode Docker / Full-Docker) sets defaults if unset: .openclaw-desktop and workspace/.
# OPENCLAW_CONFIG_DIR=./.openclaw-desktop
# OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR=./workspace
# Optional: use a pre-built image instead of local openclaw:local (see docs/install/docker.md).
# OPENCLAW_IMAGE=ghcr.io/openclaw/openclaw:latest

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Model provider API keys (set at least one)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# GEMINI_API_KEY=...
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# OPENCLAW_LIVE_OPENAI_KEY=sk-...
# OPENCLAW_LIVE_ANTHROPIC_KEY=sk-ant-...
# OPENCLAW_LIVE_GEMINI_KEY=...
# OPENAI_API_KEY_1=...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY_1=...
# GEMINI_API_KEY_1=...
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=...
# OPENAI_API_KEYS=sk-1,sk-2
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEYS=sk-ant-1,sk-ant-2
# GEMINI_API_KEYS=key-1,key-2

# Optional additional providers
# ZAI_API_KEY=...
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=...
# MINIMAX_API_KEY=...
# SYNTHETIC_API_KEY=...
#
# OpenCode Zen (bundled `opencode` provider). Free models include opencode/qwen3.6-plus-free,
# opencode/minimax-m2.5-free, opencode/gpt-5-nano, etc. See https://opencode.ai/docs/zen
# OPENCODE_API_KEY=...
# OPENCODE_ZEN_API_KEY=...   # alias recognized by some tooling
# When agents.defaults.model.fallbacks lists multiple OpenCode Zen free models, the gateway
# rotates their order each run (state: <agentDir>/opencode-zen-free-rotation.json).
# Set to 0/false/off to keep the configured order unchanged.
# OPENCLAW_ROTATE_OPENCODE_ZEN_FREE=0

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Channels (only set what you enable)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:ABCDEF...
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
# SLACK_APP_TOKEN=xapp-...

# Optional channel env fallbacks
# MATTERMOST_BOT_TOKEN=...
# MATTERMOST_URL=https://chat.example.com
# ZALO_BOT_TOKEN=...
# OPENCLAW_TWITCH_ACCESS_TOKEN=oauth:...

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tools + voice/media (optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# BRAVE_API_KEY=...
# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=pplx-...
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=...

# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=...
# XI_API_KEY=...  # alias for ElevenLabs
# DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=...
